{"paperId": "cb444eb562969f3acdd962cf3128eee1b63aab48", "abstract": "This study is divided into two crucial sections. We first gathered Bangla song names and lyrics using web crawling and a dataset that was only slightly annotated. A comprehensive dataset was then thoroughly annotated across five different genres. Utilizing transformer models to classify the genre of Bangla songs was our main goal. Noteworthy accomplishments are the 94% accuracy and F1-score of csebuetnlp/banglabert. Additionally, we created a text generation system using ritog/bangla-gpt2 and flax-community/gpt2-bengali. This method allows for the development of scenario-based music material, expanding the creative possibilities for the entertainment business, by choosing the genre with the highest F1 score from the classification findings.", "venue": "2023 26th International Conference on Computer and Information Technology (ICCIT)", "year": 2023, "citationCount": 0, "influentialCitationCount": 0, "openAccessPdf": null, "tldr": {"model": "tldr@v2.0.0", "text": "Using transformer models to classify the genre of Bangla songs allows for the development of scenario-based music material, expanding the creative possibilities for the entertainment business, by choosing the genre with the highest F1 score from the classification findings."}, "embedding": {"model": "specter_v2", "vector": [-0.19340509176254272, 0.2771493196487427, -0.04163670539855957, 0.20759804546833038, -0.4515327215194702, -0.8595865368843079, 0.5554744601249695, -0.5194364190101624, 0.30536356568336487, -0.11309853941202164, 0.8267282247543335, 0.27464503049850464, -0.30037423968315125, -0.5615081787109375, -0.12949548661708832, -0.3536384105682373, -0.3976949155330658, 0.696113646030426, -0.38139522075653076, -0.5038313269615173, 0.16574932634830475, -0.5412324666976929, -1.2606395483016968, 0.429980993270874, 0.14422905445098877, 0.43239516019821167, -0.12054954469203949, 1.2380510568618774, -0.40471452474594116, 0.38781920075416565